            <h2>Hello, Nihao and Marhaban</h2>
            <p>I'm Haomiao, a Software Development Engineer at Amazon Web Services (AWS).</p>
            <p>Previously, I graduated from Cornell University's Cornell Tech campus with a M.S. degree in Information Systems and Applied Information Sciences (with a concentration in <a class="inline-link" href="https://tech.cornell.edu/programs/masters-programs/jacobs-technion-cornell-dual-ms-connective-media/">Connective Media</a>). I have been advised by <a class="inline-link" href="https://people.jacobs.cornell.edu/mor/">Prof. Mor Naaman</a> and <a class="inline-link" href="https://nixdell.com/">Prof. Nicola Dell</a> on my reserach project centering on the relationship between YouTube's recommendation system, political extremism and misinformation. Prior to Cornell, I graduated from New York University (NYU) with a B.A. degree in <a class="inline-link" href="https://cs.nyu.edu/home/index.html">Computer Science</a> and in <a class="inline-link" href="https://as.nyu.edu/content/nyu-as/as/departments/meis.html">Middle Eastern Studies</a>.</p>
            <p>I am interested in creating all sorts of programs for social good, designing useable & useful interfaces, and creating data-driven inferences and analyses. I'm proficient in TypeScript/JavaScript, React, Python, websockets, AWS services, security best practices, technical writing, and Arabic. (Ok, I know I'm not *that* proficient with Arabic yet - but I'm getting there!)</p>
            <p>When I'm not working/studying, you can find me reading, traveling, or sampling coffee and bubble teas here in the DC area.</p>
            <p>My resume is available <a class="inline-link" href="/contact">upon request</a>.</p>
